  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Discussion On Making All Things Equal
---
There is nothing in the world bigger than the tip of an autumn hair,
and Mount T'ai is tiny. No one has lived longer than a dead child, and
P'eng-tsu died young. Heaven and earth were born at the same time I
was, and the ten thousand things are one with me.
